definitions.text: the text appearing in a book, newspaper, or other printed publication
examples: I want to see it in print

definitions.text: a picture or design printed from an engraving
a visible indication made on a surface
examples: some previous reader had covered the pages with dozens of marks
we've got to get that story into print
his book is no longer in print

definitions.text: a copy of a movie on film (especially a particular version of it)
a fabric with a dyed pattern pressed onto it (usually by engraved rollers)
a printed picture produced from a photographic negative

examples: The newspaper published the news of the royal couple's divorce
These news should not be printed

definitions.text: write as if with print; not cursive
